-- Kazakhstan Opens Probe Into Chevron Oil Venture Drilling, Novosti Reports
-- Nariman Gizitdinov
-- 2010-07-15T07:55:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/kazakhstan-opens-probe-into-chevron-oil-venture-drilling-novosti-reports.html

          
          
             Kazakhstan’s economic crimes agency
opened a probe into Chevron Corp.’s biggest venture in the
country, charging that it produced 212.4 billion tenge ($1.44
billion) of oil illegally, Novosti-Kazakhstan  reported .  
 TengizChevroil LLP drilled 41 wells to pump oil from below
5,100 meters, which is not allowed, the Astana-based news
service said, citing Murat Zhumanbai, a spokesman for the
agency. The company produced 3.4 million tons of crude from
September 2002 to June 1 from 10 wells drilled below the
official limit, Zhumanbai was cited as saying.  
 The investigation was opened July 12 based on findings from
the Prosecutor General’s Office, the news service reported.
TengizChevroil said it’s allowed produce oil without limits on
the depth of drilling, Novosti-Kazakhstan reported.  
 Maria Karazhigitova , an Atyrau-based spokeswoman for
TengizChevroil, declined to comment when reached by Bloomberg.
Zhumanbai wasn’t immediately available for comments.  
